quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  11,89,"And O my people! Let not my Shiqaq cause you to suffer the fate similar to that of the people of Nuh or of Hud or of Salih, and the people of Lut are not far off from you"
  11,90,"And ask forgiveness of your Lord and turn unto Him in repentance. Verily, my Lord is Most Merciful, Most Loving"
  11,91,"They said: \"O Shu`ayb! We do not understand much of what you say, and we see you weak among us. Were it not for your family, you would have been stoned, and you are not powerful against us"
  11,92,"He said: \"O my people! Is then my family of more weight with you than Allah And you have cast Him away behind your backs. Verily, my Lord is surrounding all that you do"
  11,93,"And O my people! Act according to your ability, and I am acting. You will come to know who it is on whom descends the torment that will cover him with ignominy, and who is a liar! And watch you! Verily, I too am watching with you"
  11,94,"And when Our commandment came, We saved Shu`ayb and those who believed with him by a mercy from Us. And As-Sayhah (awful cry) seized the wrongdoers, and they lay (Jathimin) in their homes"
  11,95,As if they had never lived there! So away with Madyan just as Thamud went away
  11,96,And indeed We sent Musa with Our Ayat and a manifest authority
  11,97,"To Fir`awn and his chiefs, but they followed the command of Fir`awn, and the command of Fir`awn was no right guide"